AIM

To write a simple C++ program that works as a CGI script and sends HTML output to a web browser.

ALGORITHM

Start the program.
Include the <iostream> header for input/output.
Print the required HTTP header "Content-type: text/html" followed by a blank line.\
Print an HTML page using C++ cout.
End the program.

CODE:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Mandatory HTTP header
    cout << "Content-type: text/html\n\n";

    // HTML output
    cout << "<html>";
    cout << "<head><title>C++ Web Program</title></head>";
    cout << "<body>";
    cout << "<h1>Hello from C++ CGI Program!</h1>";
    cout << "<p>This webpage is generated using a C++ program.</p>";
    cout << "</body>";
    cout << "</html>";

    return 0;
}

OUTPUT:
Hello from C++ CGI Program!
This webpage is generated using a C++ program.


Displayed inside a properly formatted HTML page.

RESULT

The C++ program successfully generates an HTML webpage using CGI, demonstrating how C++ can be used in web programming by sending HTML content to the browser.
